cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper deals with word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses methods for making word spaces interpretable, which involves linear algebra and machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for making word spaces interpretable, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates the methods on lexicon induction and set-based word analogy, which are tasks related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV), respectively.
